article.description: — Colbey Ross had 22 points as Pepperdine defeated San Francisco 76-68 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Ross scores 22 to lead Pepperdine over San Francisco 76-68
article.linkText: Ross scores 22 to lead Pepperdine over San Francisco 76-68
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- — Colbey Ross had 22 points as Pepperdine defeated San Francisco 76-68 on Wednesday. Sedrick Altman had 15 points for Pepperdine (9-8, 5-3 West Coast Conference). Jan Zidek added 14 points and Kessler Edwards had 13 points and 11 rebounds. Pepperdine totaled 51 points in the second half, a season best. Khalil Shabazz had 20 points for the Dons (10-9, 4-5). Isaiah Hawthorne added 13 points and Josh Kunen had eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
